public abstract class ClassicIMR
extends IntensityMeasureRelationship
implements ClassicIMRAPI

Title: ClassicIMR

Description: This subclass of IntensityMeasureRealtionship is an implementation of what's traditionally been called an "Attenuation Relationship". The shaking is assumed to follow a Gaussian distribution, which is why there's a getMean() and a getStdDev() method in addition to the getExceedProbability() method of its parent class. For this subclass of IMR the value field of the Intensity-Measure Parameter must be a Double. As an abstract class, this implements the basic functionality common to all subclasses. Various parameters and their attributes (*_NAME, *_UNITS, *_INFO *_DEFAULT,*_MIN, *_MAX) are declared here to encourage the use of uniform convenstions. Some of these parameters are instantiated in the various init* methods here, some are not. If subclasses do not need these params, they can be ignored. They can also be overridden if different attributes are desired.

pgaParam - a WarningDoubleParameter representing the Peak Ground Acceleration Intensity-Measure parameter. This parameter is instantiated in its entirety in the initSupportedIntenistyMeasureParams() method here.
PGA_NAME = "PGA"
PGA_UNITS = "g"
PGA_INFO = "Peak Ground Acceleration"
PGA_MIN = 0
PGA_MAX = Double.MAX_VALUE
PGA_WARN_MIN - see code
PGA_WARN_MAX - see code
PGA_DEFAULT - see code

pgvParam - a WarningDoubleParameter representing the Peak Ground Velocity Intensity-Measure parameter. This parameter is not instantiated here due to limited use.
PGV_NAME = "PGV"
PGV_UNITS = "g"
PGV_INFO = "Peak Ground Acceleration"
PGV_MIN = 0
PGV_MAX = Double.MAX_VALUE
PGV_WARN_MIN - see code
PGV_WARN_MAX - see code
PGV_DEFAULT - see code

saParam - a WarningDoubleParameter representing the Response Spectral Acceleration Intensity-Measure Parameter This parameter is instantiated in its entirety in the initSupportedIntenistyMeasureParams() method here. However its periodParam independent- parameter must be created and added in subclasses.
SA_NAME = "SA"
SA_UNITS = "g"
SA_INFO = "Response Spectral Acceleration"
SA_MIN = 0
SA_MAX = Double.MAX_VALUE
SA_WARN_MIN - see code
SA_WARN_MAX - see code
SA_DEFAULT - see code

periodParam - a DoubleDiscreteParameter representing the Period associated with the Response-Spectral-Acceleration Parameter (periodParam is an independentParameter of saParam). This must be created and added to saParam in subclasses.
PERIOD_NAME = "SA Period"
PERIOD_UNITS = "sec"
PERIOD_INFO = "Oscillator Period for SA"
PERIOD_DEFAULT = new Double( 0 )
Constraint is created and added in sublclasses

dampingParam - a DoubleDiscreteParameter representing the Damping level associated with the Response-Spectral-Acceleration Parameter (dampingParam is an independentParameter of saParam). This parameter is instantiated in its entirety in the initSupportedIntenistyMeasureParams() method here. This must be added to saParam in subclasses. If damping values besides 5% are available, add them in subclass and then set to non-editable.
DAMPING_NAME = "SA Damping"
DAMPING_UNITS = " % "
DAMPING_INFO = "Oscillator Damping for SA"
DAMPING_DEFAULT = new Double( 5.0 )
Constraint is created and added in sublclasses

magParam - a WarningDoubleParameter representing the earthquake moment Magnitude
MAG_NAME = "Magnitude". This parameter is created in the initPotentialEarthquakeParams() method here, but the warning constraint must be created and added in subclasses.
There are no units for Magnitude
MAG_INFO = "Earthquake Moment Magnatude"
MAG_DEFAULT - see code
MAG_MIN - see code
MAG_MAX - see code

componentParam - a StringParameter representing the Components of shaking that the IMR supports.
COMPONENT_NAME = "Component"
There are no units for Component
COMPONENT_DEFAULT = "Average Horizontal"
COMPONENT_AVE_HORZ = "Average Horizontal"
COMPONENT_RANDOM_HORZ = "Random Horizontal"
COMPONENT_VERT = "Vertical";
COMPONENT_INFO = "Component of shaking"
Constraint will be created and added in subclass

vs30Param - A WarningDoubleParameter representing the average 30-meter shear- wave velocity at the surface of a site. This parameter is created in the initSiteParams() method here, but the warning constraint must be created and added in subclasses.
VS30_NAME = "Vs30"
VS30_UNITS = "m/sec"
VS30_INFO = "Average 30 meter shear wave velocity at surface"
VS30_DEFAULT - see code
VS30_MIN = - see code
VS30_MAX = - see code

stdDevTypeParam - A StringParameter representing the various types of standard deviations that an IMR might support; "Total" is the most common (see description below for more details)
STD_DEV_TYPE_NAME = "Std Dev Type"
STD_DEV_TYPE_INFO = "Type of Standard Deviation"
STD_DEV_TYPE_DEFAULT = "Total"
STD_DEV_TYPE_TOTAL = "Total"
STD_DEV_TYPE_INTER = "Inter-Event"
STD_DEV_TYPE_INTRA = "Intra-Event"

fltTypeParam - A StringParameter representing different styles of faulting; options are specified in subclasses because nomenclature varies
FLT_TYPE_NAME = "Fault Type"
No units for this one
FLT_TYPE_INFO = "Style of faulting"

Note: SWR - SetAll() is not truly robust in case of error.

setAll

public void setAll(PotentialEarthquake potentialEarthquake,
                   Site site,
                   ParameterAPI intensityMeasure)
            throws ParameterException,
                   IMRException,
                   ConstraintException
Sets the potentialEarthquake, site, and intensityMeasure objects simultaneously.

SWR: Warning - this function doesn't provide full rollback in case of failure. There are 4 method calls that sets parameters with new values. If one function fails, the previous functions effects are not undone, i.e. the transaction is not handled gracefully.

This will take alot of design and work so it is held off for now until it is decided that it is needed.

initCoefficients

protected abstract void initCoefficients()
This function populates the hashtable of coefficients (if there are any for the subclass). The hashtable keys vary among subclasses, but are generally the intensityMeasure name plus other strings (separated by "/") that distinguish coefficient sets.

initSupportedIntensityMeasureParams

protected void initSupportedIntensityMeasureParams()
This creates the following parameters for subclasses: saParam; dampingParam, and pgaParam; the periodParam (one of saParam's independent parameters) is created and added in subclasses. All these parameters are added to the supportedIMParams list in subclasses. Note: this must generally be executed after the initCoefficients() method. lists:

initSiteParams

protected void initSiteParams()

initPotentialEarthquakeParams

protected void initPotentialEarthquakeParams()
Creates the following potential-Earthquake Parameters for subclasses: magParam (moment Magnitude parameter). Warning constraints must be created and added in subclasses. This parameter is also added to the potentialEarthquakeParams list in subclasses.

initPropagationEffectParams

protected abstract void initPropagationEffectParams()
Creates any Propagation-Effect related parameters and adds them to the propagationEffectParams list

initOtherParams

protected abstract void initOtherParams()
Creates other Parameters that the mean or stdDev depends upon, such as the Component or StdDevType parameters.

initStdDevIndependentParamsList

protected abstract void initStdDevIndependentParamsList()
Adds all parameters that StdDev depends upon to the stdDevIndependentParams list:
NOTE: This doesn not include the intensity-measure parameters or any of thier internal independentParamaters. This must be executed after the parameters have been created.

initMeanIndependentParamsList

protected abstract void initMeanIndependentParamsList()
Adds all parameters that the Mean depends upon to the MeanIndependentParams list. NOTE: This doesn not include the intensity-measure parameters or any of thier internal independentParamaters. This must be executed after the parameters have been created.
